    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This high-revving engine utilizes individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver 333 hp with a distinct metallic rasp. Power is managed through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and sent to the rear wheels via a limited-slip M-Differential. This example is mechanically robust, with documented subframe reinforcement and cooling system overhauls already completed. The suspension maintains its original geometry with upgraded polyurethane bushings for enhanced turn-in response. While showing minor signs of road use consistent with its age, the car remains an exceptional performer with linear power delivery and the communicative steering rack that defined an era of longitudinal chassis balance.",
